						<summary>

						<p>A pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> at the entrance into the same temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records that a pillar <hi rend="italic">(kāl)</hi> was created by a certain Kōṉaṅguḍaiyāṉ-baṭṭaṉ Tēṉavan Daṉapālaṉ who prayed for a son and got one named Uḍappiṟappaḻagiyāṉ.</p>						

